# Aetheris Vision — Website
# Next.js 16 App Router | TypeScript | Tailwind CSS 4 | Vercel

## Project Identity
- Business: Aetheris Vision LLC (EIN 33-4818538)
- Live URL: aetherisvision.com
- Repo: github.com/aetherisvision/aetheris-vision-website
- SSH remote: git@github-business:aetherisvision/aetheris-vision-website.git
- Deploy: push to `main` → Vercel auto-deploys (no manual deploy steps needed)

## Stack
- Framework: Next.js 16 App Router (src/app/ directory routing)
- Language: TypeScript — strict mode, no `any` types ever
- Styling: Tailwind CSS 4
- Database: Neon serverless Postgres (@neondatabase/serverless) — never use Prisma, use raw SQL
- Auth: NextAuth.js custom magic-link flow
  - Use getToken() NOT getServerSession() in App Router
  - Flow: /api/auth/send-magic → /client/confirm → /api/auth/magic
- Payments: Stripe (STRIPE_SECRET_KEY + STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET in Vercel env)
- E-signing: Docuseal API
- Site lock: src/proxy.ts — basic-auth via PREVIEW_PASSWORD env var (default: marston-av)

## Key Files
- src/lib/constants.ts — SITE object (legalName, email, tagline, etc.) — always source business facts from here
- src/lib/chat-context.ts — chat widget context
- src/lib/posts.ts — blog post helpers
- src/lib/stripe.ts — Stripe helpers

## Route Structure
- /admin/* — protected by ADMIN_PASSPHRASE cookie via proxy.ts — flag any changes here
- /client/* — magic-link authenticated client portal
- /api/auth/* — auth endpoints

## Database
- Neon endpoint: ep-frosty-sound-a8jtvtas (Azure East US 2)
- Always use @neondatabase/serverless for queries
- No ORM — raw SQL only

## Business-only repo
- **`.envrc`** loads **only** Aetheris Vision LLC secrets (`scripts/bw-envrc-av.sh`). Personal API keys belong in `~/.zshrc.local`, not here. Policy: `../aetherisvision/infrastructure/env_separation.md`.
- **Monitor business stack:** `npm run monitor:business` (Neon + Vercel) — see `../aetherisvision/infrastructure/business_stack_monitoring.md`.

## Gmail receipt scanner → Neon `expenses` (automated)
- **Route:** `src/app/api/cron/receipts/route.ts` — `GET /api/cron/receipts`
- **Trigger:** Vercel Cron (`vercel.json`) — `0 11 * * *` (11:00 UTC daily; ~6 AM US Central in standard time)
- **Auth:** `Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>` (Vercel injects); route returns 401 without it
- **Flow:** Loads Gmail OAuth **refresh tokens** from `oauth_tokens` (`biz` = business account, `per` = personal). For each connected account, queries Gmail for messages from **known vendor domains** + receipt-like subject keywords, parses first `$` amount from body text, dedupes by `gmail_message_id`, optionally uploads first PDF attachment to **Vercel Blob** (`receipts/gmail/...`), then `INSERT` into `expenses` (`source` like `gmail-biz` / `gmail-per`)
- **Vendor allowlist:** `VENDORS` const in the same file — add a row `[displayName, 'sender-domain.com', 'Category']` to recognize new merchants
- **OAuth setup:** `/admin/gmail` — connects accounts via `src/app/api/auth/gmail/*` (stores refresh token in `oauth_tokens`)
- **Manual entry / UI:** `/admin/expenses` — `POST /api/expenses` and receipt upload APIs also write to `expenses`
- **Env (Vercel):** `GMAIL_CLIENT_ID`, `GMAIL_CLIENT_SECRET`, `CRON_SECRET`, plus `BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN` for uploads; Google Cloud project must have Gmail API enabled. One-time token acquisition: `scripts/gmail-auth.ts` (see file header comment in the cron route)
- **Schema:** `src/lib/db/schema.ts` — `expenses` includes `gmail_message_id` (unique), `receipt_url`, `source`, `tax_year`

